So I found out today that Ashley is coming to Garden in 18 days for debate. I can't wait to see her. I hardly get a chance to visit her when I go to Hays. It's rather sad. We had a test in math today and I think I did ok. Better than I was expecting actually. Afterschool my sister and I bought mac and cheese and came home and made it. It was really good. I sat down and ate that and studied for my test in Intro To Drama tonight. I'm gunna need some prayers to pass that one. Oh well. Guys honestly, I feel really alone. It sucks being in love with someone you can't have for reasons beyond your control. she needs to hear she's beautiful

Yeah, sorry I haven't been updating like I've promised so many times.  
I'm still single, go figure.  I feel like shit...emotionally, physically and mentally.  I really need a break.  

I'm hoping to get my pictures from the Cheifs game back soon, so I can post them.  We had great seats...the 11th row...right behind the endzone.   

I'm gunna go do some homework.  Bye.

Lately, my life has just been a mess of problems, worthless bullshit, and drama. None of it worthy of posting. So I'll spare you the agony and skip through all the events of past weeks. Yesterday was overall a good day. Sarah and I drove around for a bit then I dropped her off after school. Then I cleaned my room as so I could go out for the night. At around 6, Sarah dropped by for a bit and I decided to leave with her. I talked to several of the band kids and then met up with Breanna at the football game. The football game was very fun. I talked to alot of people I hadn't talked to in a while and had a great time. After half time my interest in the game withered away so I went off to talk to some friends. I saw Amadeus and Billy and decided to talk to them. Hallie came up and we all sat there for a while. My sister then came up and showed me this cockroach she had found. She had it on a blanket. Hallie told her to put it in someone's hair. So my sister decided her prey was going to be this girl who had been spreading rumors and saying shit about my sister. The girl had no clue she had a bug in her hair for the most part and she still didn't when my sister and her friends walked away laughing. It was great. After the game, I came home and watched the party at Levi's house. Today, I plan to hang out with Billy for a bit. The orginal plans were for Sarah, Billy, Alex and I to hang out. But Sarah has to work and Alex well....he's just not coming. So it's down to Billy and I. That should be fun though. After that I'm hanging out with Sarah. (hopefully if her mom isn't being stupid). Oh well. "Never take it seriously. If you never take it seriously you never get hurt. If you never get hurt then you always have fun."

So, I got a car. That's about all thats worth updating about it. I don't know...maybe something interesting will happen in the next few days and I'll update about it...I"m just not in the mood. Sorry guys....
Man, I feel terrible.  I can't even bring myself to explain why I feel this way.  So i'm going to end this post before I even get started.  Maybe I'll explain more later.  Sorry.

Ok, sorry for my lack of updates.  I could lie and say I've been busy, but I'm against lieing so I won't.  Truth is I haven't been busy at all.
  
Tyler and I broke up as many of you may or may not know.  Frankly I hardly think it makes much of a difference, I'm still the same Rachel, nothings different except for the fact that I no longer have a boyfriend.  Big deal.  

All I've done lately is catch up with some friends I neglected while dating Tyler and made amends with them.   I've also gone to a few college classes those are working out pretty well.   

Blah, this is a boring update...and I'm sorry.

So here I am sitting here feeling worthless.  My plans fell through once again.  I want to cry but I know this is one of those times I need to suck it up and be a big girl.  But sometimes it's just so hard to pretend like you're okay when you aren't.  I'm not happy with myself or my friends.  I'm not happy with my love life.   I can't stand feeling like this, and I hate complaining.  I'm about ready to just tell everyone exactly how I feel, but that wouldn't be good.  Gosh, I'm sick of this update.  I'm going for a walk.  Good Bye.

Here's to a great first day of school...not. I'll keep this simple and give you a rundown of my classes. First off, we have Spanish II with Mrs. Pinon, let me tell you I'm not to thrilled about this one. But with Kyle Blackburn, Tyler Dechant, Sam Nelson and Sarah Cruz it should be some fun. After that it was off to Art I with Mr. Simpson; Hallie H., Ryan L., Brynn H. and Ryker made that a semi fun class for the morning. Right after that I had Algebra II most of the class from last year was there so I can already tell this is gunna be a fun class, besides the fact that it's math. After lunch I had Aerobics I have that class with Janee S. and Hillary V. so it should amount to some fun. Right after that I had World History same kids from last year. I hardly get along with that crowd anymore:( Oh well, I like the teacher well enough. Then it was Chemistry Jay's in that class with me and so is Kylie...I talked to Jay mostly only cause he's my favorite person right now. Then English II eh I liked the teacher, kind of. But the kids in that class bore me. Blah, I love English tho. So today in English I overheard an old friend of mine bashing his own brother for turning "punk rock". I about reached over and slapped him. Gosh people are so disrespectful. He really needs to learn some r-e-s-p-e-c-t. Or I'm gunna have to teach him some. I mean he's the popular jock who everyone wants to be and here he is bashing things he doesn't know. How fucking ignorant. I swear if he says something about it tomorrow I'm going to lose my cool. Eh, on a lighter note. I did my english homework and hung out with Tyler and Jay. Jay played PS2 for almost 3 hours haha he almost beat the entire Tony Hawk Underground game, he only had like 10 min left when Tyler's mom called. Ha, oh well. Well tomorrow I'm off to Hays after school. It should be some fun. I'll get to see Addie and Ashley I'm pretty excited about that. Well I'm done...good night

So, I signed up for some college classes.  On Monday nights I have Intro To Drama and on Tuesday nights I'll have World Geography.  Yay for me. Now I'll have something to do.  Blah.  I'm going to be pretty busy this first semester so I might get a little stressful.  Oh well I'm ready to make some progress.  

Sarah spent the night last night.  It was fun.  We ate most of a frozen pizza and drank some dr. pepper and stayed up late talking.  blah.  it was fun.  

I have to admit I'm still upset about the Kylie thing.  I don't know why I'm letting it get to me.  But I guess I'm just afraid to let go.  

I think I'm gunna go drive around with Tyler.  So bye for now.  Expect an update later.
P.S. Who ever stole Jon's Fall Out Boy, is mine.

Wow I love starting trends...like the bold all that apply to you from a list of 100 items...yeah I wish people would have picked up my trend of putting it behind an LJ cut. It totally killed my friend page. My friend's page is already murderous to load onto my computer because of my new transparent layout and now I have random lists of 100 things. Blah I love complaining:). The infamous Ryan story. Ok, for those of you who know Ryan you might understand this mroe than those who don't know him. Well him and Tyler do not get along anymore. Ryan's mother seems to think that it's my fault. So she calls a meeting at Tyler's house and brings the cops. Tyler told them I couldn't go, which I couldn't cause I was at the show. Well Ryan's mom says some mean things about me, like that she knows my type and she knows my attitude and that she's never liked me from the moment she's met me (speaking of which I didn't meet the lady until Saturday, the day after she said all this) Well Ryan's mom and Tyler's mom decide to come to my house and read Ryan and I's msn conversations. Growl. They didn't succeed and I had to print them off for the both of them. So to make a long story short I had a bad weekend and Ryan and I are no longer friends. I think trying to become friends with old friends is just overrated. I'm trying to become friends with Kylie again and after all my efforts it's not working. I had invited her to spend the night Saturday night, she told me her dad said she needed to wake up early the next day so she couldn't spend the night. So I said well we should still hang out. And she said sure and decided she wanted to take a nap. She told me she'd call when she woke up. Well she also said she was setting her alarm to go off in 30 min. Well after 2 hours she still hadn't called so I called her. And she told me that she'd ask her mom and call me back in 5 min. 15 minutes later she called and said she was really tired so she was staying home. So I went to Tylers. Well Jay tells me to call Kylie and I call her only to find out she's at Victorias. I was crushed. I offically give up trying to be her friend. I told her that the ball is in her court now and she can do with it as she pleases. Eh, it's a harsh world, love. Once school starts I promise I'll update regularly. Plus I'll probably have more to update when I actually do stuff. You never loved me like you said you did

You Know You're From Kansas When...
You've been hit by enough tornados to know there is no such thing as Oz You can properly pronounce Salina, Basehor, Schoenchen, Olathe & Osawatomie A shotgun is your idea of instant messaging. You learned how to shoot a gun before you learned how to multiply You're ready to shoot the next person who asks about Toto & Dorthy You've had classes canceled for heat & snow in the same month You support the Chiefs through thick and thin. You have to travel 20 miles just to go to the nearest mall The only tourists you see are on the way to Colorado You know the meaning of Rock Chalk Jayhawk. Your closest neighbor is more than a mile away, and you can still see him from your front porch. The terms Sooners, Huskers and Missouri Tigers cause the hairs on the back of your neck to stand up straight and your blood pressure to rise. You are not surprised to find movie rentals, ammunition and bait all in the same store. You know everything goes better with Ranch. You know the real way to pronounce the name of Clintons state and the river... arKANSAS. You never met any celebrities. (Bob Dole isn't a celebrity, he's your neighbor.) You prefer the Little Apple over the Big Apple as a place to live. You had at least one summer job that was bucking bails or custom cutting. You understand the difference between 3.2 and 6 point, and more than once you've made a beer run to another state. You know in your heart that K-State can beat Oklahoma in football. You call that smell coming from the feed yards "money." You know that Mt. Oread is really only just a hill. Down south means Oklahoma. You can properly pronounce Basehor, Cimmeron, Schoenchen, Kechi, Chautauqua, Arkalalah, and Osawatomie. You really do think Sunflowers are beautiful. You went to skating parties as a kid. You'll pay for your kids to go to college...unless they want to go to OU or NU. Your earliest driving lessons were in a field while picking up hay. Your excuse for being late is the cows got out, and the boss accepts it MANY times Your main drag in town is two blocks long. You actually get these jokes and pass them on to other friends from Kansas.

Last night was pretty fun.  We all decided to go out to the haunted houses or more like abandoned houses because I don't believe in all that ghost stuff.  Well there were a ton of people out there so it wasn't scary at all.  We all walked through the first house and decided to head back into town.  On the way into town we all stopped at the railroad cars to see if we could get in.  We found a bunch of bones but we figured they were just animal bones.  Then we scared Susan because had found a hand or well a cow hoof but from our angle it looked like a human hand. So Brevan decides to pick it up and show Susan, in turn Susan screams and we all get a good laugh.  I have to admit for as scared as Susan was she is a pretty brave person. More than half of the group wouldn't even come near the railroad cars.  Well Tyler, Jay and I started to go back into town so I could get home and we took Devin with us cause he had to be home too.  Susan, Jon, Brevan, and Justin decided to go to the other haunted house.  Jon turned the car off and left the light on because he was scared, in turn running the battery down.  Well meanwhile we are on our way home.  Then we get a phone call from Jon and them saying the car wont start.  Now they are out by a haunted house in the middle of no where scared shitless so we turn around and go help them.  Needless to say I was home late. But it was a fun night.

After I finished cleaning Sarah came over and we got some money to go to Target.  We opened up the door and Jeff was there.  So we made him follow us to target. People always tell me not to listen to what other people say.  But if I did what they told me I'd be listening to what other people say.  I'm so confused.  I've concluded that what people say has a very big impact on me.  Like a few days ago, Tiffany Lefort was giving me shit.  I'm not sure why but I'm sure Tiffany Baxter was involved with what most of Lefort was saying.  Lefort was giving me shit for the way I act, dress, and talk.  She says I dress too preppy and act too "punk" she also told me that I'm not that smart and to stop talking like I am because it's annoying.  This just pissed me off.  And I'm still pissed about it even though it was several days ago.  I'm in a terrible mood.

Anyways enough of that.  Yesterday I was awoken by the doorbell.  Sarah Trimble had decided to come over without calling, something that bugs me very much.  But I hung out with her for a while and decided to mow since I needed to.  I mowed, and changed my clothes.  Then Sarah and I went off to do some shopping.  Sarah bought some bracelets and I bought nothing cause I had insufficent funds.  Well we were walking back to her car and I shoved my hands in my back pockets and I found $11 dollars folded up in my pocket.  I swear I haven't been that happy in a while.  So Sarah and I decided to go get some lunch even though it was about 2.  After we ate we went to Tyler's to see the car they got.  Actually it was just a totalled Acura Integra they got to fix Tyler's car.  We left and went to Target and Walmart then back to our respectable homes.

I stayed at home for a while and took a shower.  Then I called Sarah and her and I went to Florence Wilson for a good 15 minutes.  We decided to go for a walk.  We walked all over our neighborhood and other peoples neighborhoods as well.  We went back to her house and she gave me a ride home.  

At about 9:30 I went and hung out with Jay and Tyler, after getting yelled at from my mom for about 30 minutes about how she's worried about me.  She thinks I'm going to be a dumb alcoholic/pothead/dropout by the time i'm going to be 16.  It's pathetic.  Oh well I guess she's just trying to be a good mom.  But Ty and Jay and I went and caught up with Soren and Kiel.  At about 10:30 we all came back to my house for a while.  Kiel, Soren and Jay went to go look at Enrique's car and Tyler and I sat on my front porch and talked.  The rest of them came back and they all let to go to Trent's and I got on the computer...end of the night. 

So today I woke up several times and just laid in bed because it's so comfortable.  Then the phone rang so I answered it and talked to Tyler for a while.  Then I got up and watched some TV.  I watched City Confidental, good show, then I watched Cribs for like 15 minutes.  Now I'm here eating a pb&j and writing a too long of post.  There I think i'm finished updating for a while.

There was quit a screaming match and Brittany left trying to avoid a fight. I mean 18-13....Brittany is smarter than to go to jail for something that stupid. Well to make a long story short Brittany and Shannon eventually made up. Brittany gave me and shannon both rides home and on the way to my house. I've noticed that ranting has become an ever popular posting subject in recent months so I decided to give it a try and have my self a little bitch fest. I haven't done this alot recently so wish me luck....starting...NOW! Ok well there is this guy...Let's call him Kiel, well that's because that is his name. Hopefully he doesn't read this but if he does then I guess he'll understand my point a tad bit better. Well you see Kiel and I dated and we recently broke up...blah blah blah, story of my life. He went to Missouri two days after we broke up. During his week long stay in Missouri I was asked out by another guy that I had my eye on several months ago but never had the heart to ask out, well to make a short story long, I said yes. The "guy" that I am dating now and I decided that we aren't going to go around annoucing that we are together, just to avoid the drama that my friends like to create. But slowly people have started to notice that we are always together and started to pick it up from there. Well when Kiel came back to town he was informed of my new boyfriend, well this is where the confusion happens. You see Kiel thinks I broke up with him because I didn't want a boyfriend...which is not what I told him nor what I told anyone else, I think he made that up in his head because the words "I don't want a boyfriend" were never said, I think it was something more like "When we started dating I wasn't ready for a relationship this serious" I don't know it was more than a week ago. So now Kiel thinks that I am trying to hide my relationship from him...which is not what I am doing. First off if I was trying to hide it I wouldn't have told him in the first place. I mean seriously I was holding his hand at the zoo right in next to Kiel...if I was trying to hide it from him would I do that? Well this whole situation is ludacris and Kiel is still mad about it and doesn't understand my side which I have tried to explain to him and several other people. Another thing that bothers me is when I find out that people think I do not like them. I'm a very nice person and usually like everyone until they give me a good enough reason not too...then I usually give them a couple more chances to get in my good graces. Well several girls have gone around saying that I don't like them which is very untrue and actually makes me feel rather bad. I think tonight I shall talk to them seeing as I have never really had a conversation with them. Also recently I've discovered that I'm not as happy with my friends as I thought I was. I'm being pulled into this big mess of drama that I extremely dislike. Also the sex, drugs and alcohol thing gets old and stresses me out. I'd like to get as far away from that as possible, but it seems that is all teens are involved with these days. Ok this post is longer than intended...my apologizes. [Edit] I apologized to kiel and set him straight with the story so we are friends again Yay
